com.r3.corda.networkmanage.common.cryptoservice

Class JCACryptoService<T extends AuthenticationCredentials,U extends KeyConfig>

  • com.r3.corda.networkmanage.common.cryptoservice.JCACryptoService<T,U>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CryptoService<T,U>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AmazonCloudHsmCryptoService, GemaltoLunaCryptoService, SecurosysPrimusXCryptoService

    public class JCACryptoService<T extends AuthenticationCredentials,U extends KeyConfig>
implements CryptoService<T,U>

    This is the base class that facilitates easy integration of further HSM vendors that provide a JCA provider. For every vendor we want to support there has to be a new CryptoService that implements interface CryptoService and optionally inherits from this class if it makes sense. Not all vendors fully implement the JCA API and some of the methods of this class will have to be overridden with vendor-specific implementations.

    It is required that @keyStore is initialized.

    See Also:
    interface CryptoService
